# LCD Digits

Inspired by [TDD-Katas](https://github.com/garora/TDD-Katas/blob/master/KatasReadme.md), with some extra bonus rounds ðŸ˜Š

> Your task is to create an LCD string representation of an
> integer value using a 3x3 grid of space, underscore, and
> pipe characters for each digit. Each digit is shown below
> (using a dot instead of a space)
> 
> ```
> ._.   ...   ._.   ._.   ...   ._.   ._.   ._.   ._.   ._.
> |.|   ..|   ._|   ._|   |_|   |_.   |_.   ..|   |_|   |_|
> |_|   ..|   |_.   ._|   ..|   ._|   |_|   ..|   |_|   ..|
> ```
> 
> Example: `910` would render:
> 
> ```
> ._. ... ._.
> |_| ..| |.|
> ..| ..| |_|
> ```
> 
> _Spec from [TDD-Katas](https://github.com/garora/TDD-Katas/blob/master/KatasReadme.md#lcd-digits-)._

---

## Bonus Rounds âœ¨

### #1 Light it up!

Render gaps as blanks, digits as lime/red. For example:

<div style="font-family:monospace">
    ...&nbsp;.<span style="color:lime">_</span>.<br>
    <span style="color:lime">|_|</span>&nbsp;.<span style="color:lime">_|</span><br>
    ..<span style="color:lime">|</span>&nbsp;<span style="color:lime">|_</span>.<br>
</div>

---

### #2 What's the time?

Use this code to make an LCD clock - using your current sytem time (add seconds to get things moving). **Note:** You'll need separators, so using all those dots might not work so well ðŸ˜‰

---

### #3 Coding like a `22032Ã·4`!

Make a simple calculator! To [KISS][kiss], only support basic addition, subtraction multiply and divide.
`6427x5` the day! Are these words `(378x10000)+1637`? Let's take LCD around the `43312-5236`!

You can go to town with this if you can make some sums that result in [these numbers](http://blog.presentandcorrect.com/250-words-you-can-spell-with-a-calculator).


[kiss]:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KISS_principle